{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 09:40:14.620346", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nSummary\n- The EBGP-based Clos fabric (super-spine, spines, leaves) is operational. All inter-router links are up, BGP sessions are established, and expected prefixes are present in RIB/FIB across tiers.\n- End-host pc_0_0 is not participating in the network: it has no Ethernet interface configured (only loopback), no IP, and no routing. This is the primary anomaly and the root cause of host-to-host failure.\n- Host pc_0_1 is correctly configured and can reach the remote leaf router interface, confirming the fabric is forwarding correctly.\n\nKey Observations and Evidence\n1) Host state\n- pc_0_0:\n  - No eth interfaces present; only loopback exists.\n  - No IP addresses (beyond 127.0.0.1) and no routes.\n  - Evidence: get_host_net_config(pc_0_0) shows only lo, empty ip_route; ip link on pc_0_0 lists only lo.\n- pc_0_1:\n  - Interface eth0 up with 10.0.1.2/24 and default route via 10.0.1.1.\n  - Evidence: get_host_net_config(pc_0_1).\n\n2) Data-plane reachability tests from pc_0_1\n- Ping to 10.0.0.1 (leaf_router_0_0 SVI) succeeds with low RTTs.\n  - Evidence: ping pc_0_1 -> 10.0.0.1: 0% loss.\n- Ping to 10.0.0.2 (expected pc_0_0 host IP) fails with “Destination Host Unreachable” returned by 172.16.0.5 (leaf_router_0_0).\n  - Evidence: ping pc_0_1 -> 10.0.0.2 shows ICMP host unreachable from leaf_router_0_0’s underlay address.\n  - Interpretation: The fabric forwards traffic to leaf_router_0_0 just fine; the access segment on 10.0.0.0/24 lacks a responding host (no ARP resolution/neighbor).\n\n3) Control-plane (BGP) health\n- Leaves (AS 65200 and 65201) have EBGP peering to both spines and receive the remote leaf’s prefix.\n  - Evidence: show bgp summary on leaf_router_0_0 and leaf_router_0_1 (2 peers each; State/PfxRcd = 1 per spine).\n- Spines (AS 65100 and 65101) have EBGP peering to super-spine and both leaves; they receive and advertise the two /24s.\n  - Evidence: show ip route on spines includes BGP routes to 10.0.0.0/24 and 10.0.1.0/24 via appropriate /31 links.\n- Super-spine (AS 65000) has EBGP to both spines and has routes to both /24s (selected via one spine, which is normal without multipath).\n  - Evidence: show ip route on super_spine_router_0 shows BGP routes to both 10.0.0.0/24 and 10.0.1.0/24; show bgp summary shows 2 neighbors up.\n\n4) Underlay links and addressing\n- All inter-router /31 links present and up, consistent with topology.\n  - Evidence: ifconfig/ip addr/ip route outputs on leafs and spines show the expected 172.16.0.x/31 links.\n- Leaf SVIs:\n  - leaf_router_0_0: 10.0.0.1/24 up.\n  - leaf_router_0_1: 10.0.1.1/24 up.\n\nAnomalies Detected\n- pc_0_0’s Ethernet interface is missing or down; host has no IP configuration and no connectivity to its leaf.\n- Consequence: 10.0.0.0/24 subnet has only the leaf’s SVI reachable; host 10.0.0.2 is unreachable, causing host-to-host failure from pc_0_1 to pc_0_0.\n\nFault Localization\n- Fabric (super-spine, spines, leaves) is healthy: EBGP sessions up, routes installed, and inter-VLAN/VRF forwarding functions correctly (pc_0_1 can reach remote leaf SVI).\n- The fault is localized to the access segment on pod 0 leaf 0, specifically at the host pc_0_0. The leaf router itself is functioning and reachable.\n\nRoot Cause\n- Host misconfiguration or failure on pc_0_0: no active Ethernet interface and no L3 configuration. This prevents ARP resolution and any IP communication on 10.0.0.0/24 behind leaf_router_0_0, resulting in ICMP “Destination Host Unreachable” when other endpoints try to reach 10.0.0.2.\n\nImpact Assessment\n- Inter-router and fabric-wide routing: Normal.\n- Inter-host connectivity:\n  - pc_0_1 can reach leaf_router_0_0 SVI across the fabric (OK).\n  - pc_0_1 cannot reach pc_0_0 (FAIL) due to pc_0_0 being offline/unconfigured.\n- Affected scope: Only endpoints in 10.0.0.0/24 dependent on pc_0_0; the overall Clos fabric is operational.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 9616, "output_tokens": 4301, "total_tokens": 13917, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 9344}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 3136}}}
